<br>
Also, HP is nice, AC is better, and to be able to play your class right is money.<br>
<br>
If you want to be an SK that everyone wants in their group, then fill out your offensive aa's, get your mana regen up, and go full blast dps.  As long as you can actually survive without causing the cleric to go oom in 30mins' time, they are going to take you over a paladin or warrior anyday since now they not only have an official tank, but the dps to cut through the dungeons.<br>
<br>
Here is what my &quot;offensive lineup&quot; looks like for ldon:<br>
<br>
slot 1:  engulfing darkness, used only when i see mobs actually starting to run (clinging just isnt enough snare in my opinion)<br>
<br>
slot 2: scythe of inny (if undead, if not then spear of plague which has same dmg/mana ratio as decay)<br>
<br>
slot 3: spear of decay<br>
<br>
slot 4: touch of inny (gosh dang i need the lvl65 one) or spear of plague if I find i have the mana regen and healer is doing fine.<br>
<br>
slot 5: zeph's bite<br>
<br>
slot 6: My most versatile slot, either is spear of plague (if scythe is in 2), 200dd ac tap, or terror spell<br>
<br>
slot 7: Mental corruption <br>
<br>
slot 8: FD<br>
<br>
I use every single dd in that line up (touch of inny only when i need health if healer is healing someone else), if I'm in a decent group.  If the group is made of classes who don't contribute to mana regen, pull spear of plague out, and possibly the ac tap out.  I never without casting them.  I always ask for mod rods and take pot9 over virtue.  And I always ask the bstlrd to use paragon as frequently as possible.  We go all out.  With this, I get 50dps just in spells, putting me at around 180dps. (130dps in procs, melee, and pet, easily)<br>
<br>
880+600+400+200+200=2280dmg in one minute (actually a little more, since spears repop at 45secs, but this is close enough)<br>
<br>
Throw in ID4 and you get roughly 2280*1.12=2550ish a minute<br>
<br>
Throw in critical blasts that happen 1 in 5 casts, and your average is 2550*1.2= 3060<br>
<br>
3060/60 = 50dps<br>
<br>
If you can dish out a constant 180dps as a tank...a group will take you, unless you are stupid.  And there are a lot of stupid tanks.<br>
<br>
I'm old school by the way, my weapon is a facesmasher (velious era) so I know others should be able to do this as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg>TheTribunal.org</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm29>Shadowknight</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org/">Home</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font> <!-- .. -->
